li.p:
 If A=\left(
								\begin{array}{cc}
								1 & 1 \\
								0 & 0 \\
								\end{array}
								\right) and B =\left(
								\begin{array}{cc}
								0 & -1 \\
								0 & 0 \\
								\end{array}
								\right) , use the series in part (b) to show that e^A= \left(
								\begin{array}{cc}
								e & e-1 \\
								0 & 1 \\
								\end{array}
								\right)and e^B= \left(
								\begin{array}{cc}
								1 & -1 \\
								0 & 1 \\
								\end{array}
								\right).

Show that  e^{A+B}= \left(
								\begin{array}{cc}
								e & 0 \\
								0 & 1 \\
								\end{array}
								\right).
